<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF7A6AC5FCEA94851A95B8A9" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF7A6AC5FCEA94851A95B8A9" blockId="129.[788,1380,614,1042]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF7A6AC5FCEA94851DF8B9CF" authorityName="G. M. Allen" authorityYear="1914" box="[790,1016,732,765]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altilis">Scotophilus altilis</taxonomicName>
was traditionally considered a junior synonym of S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF7A6AC5FB5C95511B26B817" box="[1184,1318,776,805]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">leucogaster</taxonomicName>
, until additional samples and molecular and morphological analyses confirmed it as a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF7A6AC5FCE995FF1F8CBF0E" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" type="multiple">
<caption id="90EB6676FF7A6AC5FCE995FF1F8CBF0E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398398" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398398/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" targetBox="[174,765,624,1038]" targetPageId="129">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF7A6AC5FCE995FF1F8CBF0E" blockId="129.[788,1380,614,1042]" lastBlockId="129.[175,1380,1051,1597]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF7A6AC5FCE995FF1DD0B8F1" bold="true" box="[789,976,934,963]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from scattered localities in SE 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF7A6AC5FB9495881AC7B8D8" box="[1128,1223,977,1002]" name="Sudan" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Sudan</collectingCountry>
, W 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF7A6AC5FAF695881D43BF20" name="Ethiopia" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, SC 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF7A6AC5FC6B95A01A5FBF20" box="[919,1119,1017,1042]" name="South Sudan" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">South Sudan</collectingCountry>
, NE 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF7A6AC5FB4B95A01B5CBF20" box="[1207,1372,1017,1042]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
, and SW 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF7A6AC5FED092421F88BF0E" box="[300,392,1051,1084]" name="Kenya" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Kenya</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF7A6AC5FF5392191CFFBE1A" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" type="description">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF7A6AC5FF5392191CFFBE1A" blockId="129.[175,1380,1051,1597]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF7A6AC5FF5392191FA9BF53" bold="true" box="[175,425,1088,1121]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Forearm c¢. 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF7A6AC5FDAD92191CB1BF53" box="[593,689,1088,1121]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" unit="mm" value="46.0">46 mm</quantity>
. Dorsal pelageis sepia-brown to pale brown; venter is light brown. Wings and uropatagium are uniformly dark brown. Ears are comparatively short and widely separated, with inner margin strongly convex and outer margin almost straight. Tragus tapers to bluntly rounded tip, with concave anterior margin. Eyes are small. Skull is medium to large (greatest skull lengths 16-5-20- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF7A6AC5FAF992871B56BFCD" box="[1285,1366,1246,1279]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
) for 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF7A6AC5FF1F935E1F70BE1A" box="[227,368,1287,1320]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scotophilus</taxonomicName>
, and sagittal crest is present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
